The drama surrounding Mau evictions is a political showdown. The parties involved in this exercise seem to stand for the interest of certain powers within the government. Environment CS Keriako Tobiko has promised to evict the ‘big fish’ owning acres of land in the vast Mau Forest. Only 40 title deeds (5,000 acres) have been surrendered to Narok county leaving 20,000 hectares under the ownership of private developers. Poor Kenyans suffer eviction threats while prominent persons in subsequent regimes continue enjoying state protection. Lang’ata